Package com.invectorate.open.queutures

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Informable<T>
    An object that performs an arbitrary computation when it is given input of a certain type.
    Queuture<V>
    A representation of the outcome of an arbitrary asynchronous computation that may generate many results.
    QueutureBox<V>
    The opaque interface that Informables that are expected to be used to generate data for Queutures use to submit new information.
    QueutureExecutorService
    An ExecutorService that also supports submitting instances of Informable to create Queutures.
    RunnableQueuture<V>
    A Queuture that can itself be executed as a Runnable.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DelegatedQueutureExecutorService
    Default implementation for QueutureExecutorService that simply forwards to a delegate executor service.
    QueutureTask<V>
    An implementation of Queuture that additionally provides the ability to run a computation.
